description.plain:
Lennon Stella (born August 13, 1999) is a singer-songwriter from from Oshawa, Ontario, who shot to internet fame at an early age with her viral video with sister Maisy Stella. The two sisters also starred in the popular country music-themed TV series Nashville.

In November 2018, Lennon launched her solo career with her debut EP Love, me. She has gone on to release several successful singles, including “Polaroid,” a high-profile collab with Jonas Blue and Liam Payne.

description.plain: “Like Everybody Else” is a song by Canadian singer-songwriter Lennon Stella, released as the first non-album single in 2018. For any young teenage girl, it just gets so hard to feel unique. There are so many options in front of your face all the time. Being young and trying to find your way and having a world full of people doing exactly what you want to do… there’s so much in your face all the time.

songs.title: Bad

description.plain: In this song, Lennon talks about how getting over her break up with someone that cheated on her would have been easier if she had “bad signs” in her relationship. When you break up with a person there are usually signs before the relationship ends that it wasn’t working out, especially having had the other person cheating on Stella, but that wasn’t the experience. Lennon recounts that, in reality, she was being treated the way she would want to be treated in a relationship and she didn’t notice anything was wrong until she found out the other person was cheating on her.
